cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the use of canonical correlation analysis (CCA) in multi-view learning, which is a common technique in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses applications in multi-modal retrieval and classification (cs.MM) and multi-view embedding (cs.AI), which further support these sub-categories.
